The paper discusses data augmentation techniques for improving the generalization performance of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a self-supervised learning framework and a knowledge transfer technique, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions few-shot and imbalanced classification scenarios, which are common topics in neural networks (cs.NE).
